Smart appliances like refrigerators and dishwashers often have notification systems that beep or chime to indicate status updates or alerts. If you're unsure about the source of the noise, you may want to investigate the user manuals for each of your appliances or check their settings to see if there are notifications being sent even when your phone is in Do Not Disturb mode.

The flickering lights could indeed be related to the lighting system in your home. Dimmer switches can sometimes cause flickering, especially if they're not designed to work with the type of light bulbs you're using.&#x20;

